This paper deals with image-to-image translation using generative adversarial networks (GANs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves regularization techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper discusses data augmentation, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) research.
